{
  "texts": [
    "We can further decrease the computational load by making each temporal and spatial layer configurable as depthwise-separable (DWS) layers, as inspired by the MobileNet models [4].",
    "Fig. 3.B shows the model performance as we increase the number of DWS layers, starting from the last layer of the backbone to the first layer 9.We measured activation sparsity in the network (over the validation set), and found it to average around 50%, about what one would expect given ReLU activation functions.",
    "Reasoning that much of this activity may not be informative, given the very high spatial sparsity of input to the network, we applied L 1 regularization to activation layers.",
    "Fig. 3.C and 3.D shows the scaling of model performance and sparsity-aware MACs as the weighting of the regularization in the loss is varied.",
    "Extraordinarily, it is apparent that the model can achieve greater than 90% sparsity while suffering minimal performance drop."
  ]
}